      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Regis Garbo, one of your Chatter respondents on May 12, wants us to feel sorry for him because gasoline prices are going up and his boat uses 250 gallons of gas in two weeks.</p>
        <p>Two hundred fifty gallons! That's like driving 7,500 miles. Has Mr. Garbo heard of global warming, or poor air quality that contributes to serious health  problems? Why does he think he has the right to contribute so much more to these problems than the rest of us?</p>
        <p>Another writer had the right idea: drive a smaller car, and drive less.  This is the responsible thing to do regardless of gas prices.</p>
        <p>REBECCA ERICKSON Hopewell</p>
      </block>
